I&#x27;m trying to get the rfcomm thing going with my new Nokia E60, so that I can go online over it from my laptop via UMTS. With my Nokia 6230 it worked right out of the box. So I did some research but haven&#x27;t found a solution yet. This story is just an anchor for some memorable links.


&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.teaparty.net&#x2F;technotes&#x2F;blue-gprs.html&quot;&gt;Tom&#x27;s Guide with 6310i&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jpberlin.de&#x2F;j.kowal&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;index.php&#x2F;Vaio_-_Bluetooth&quot;&gt;Bluetooth  on Vaio and explanation for the &quot;Address already in use&quot; error&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.integrasoftware.it&#x2F;index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=84&amp;Itemid=28&quot;&gt;
Nice KDE centric guide with screenshots&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.gentoo.org&#x2F;doc&#x2F;en&#x2F;bluetooth-guide.xml&quot;&gt;Gentoo Guide, very thorough&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.mobguru.com&#x2F;Linux+GPRS+Bluetooth.htm&quot;&gt;Yet another nice guide&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;

I also found a link to gnubox which sounds very interesting. It allows you to use your LAN to go online from your phone via bluetooth, so just the other way round. That&#x27;s of course not necessary for the E60 because it integrates WLAN. Here is a link to a &lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.unix-ag.uni-kl.de&#x2F;~leonard&#x2F;linux-n6600-howto.html&quot;&gt;Nice setup guide with the n6600&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;gnubox.dnsalias.org&#x2F;gnubox&#x2F;&quot;&gt;here is all the information you need&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.

Perhaps these links help someone.

